tle>   sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> Maybe.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/ss/JageedLongSword.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
that's almost as good as a water sprinkler, I can think of some situations I'd use it with a sarnak shield or bladestopper. <p>Nillon, level 54 champion, Brell Serilis</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 7/6/00 9:56:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tembdaraangelknight>Tembdara AngelKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/6/00 7:24:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> Just might be Nillon, I've been using my Amy Whip and Nautilus Sheild when I'm in a group with more than one Tank. I love that BONK Sound <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/6/00 7:56:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> yup viable solution<br>
<br>
i've been using mine for a while and :<br>
1) it helps increasing my AC<br>
2) it allows me to bash without switching weap and shield every 5 or so seconds<br>
3) it doesnt really affects my taunt ( off hand weapons hits less and for less damage due to a lower minimal hit and bash taunts well )<br>
<br>
i'm using a silken whip of ensnaring right now ( 14/28 effect snare ac -9 )<br>
and i guarantee you the snare effect is even better than fast weapon + dual wield to taunt ( with bash maxed at least )<br>
but i was already using it when i only had a SSOY as my main weapon and never really had any problems taunting<br>
<br>
i only give up the shield when i'm not the main tank or the puller and when i really need to taunt hardcore or to deal a lot of damage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthogthiselbashem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thog Thiselbashem</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/7/00 9:47:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> To large races its not that viable.  We can already bash.  At level 55 all warriors can stun with there kick(not sure how this compares to slam).  I find that there are very few occasions where that little bit of extra AC would help.  They need a warrior sword that allows and forces us to use a shield but not be reduced to paladin type damage.  Our main job is to taunt so I choose to stick to dw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/7/00 2:09:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> Well, in those situations where my survivability is at stake, perhaps.. but since I can bash, and most of my role is to keep things taunted, I'd probably stick to duel wield. Wouldn't mind wielding one of these babies though. With a snare whip in the other hand i'd be the taunt machine.<br>
<br>
Thoric Frosthammer<br>
Silent Redemption <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/7/00 10:13:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> i dont use my shield for bash<br>
if i want to just bash i can dual wield and bash at the same time with a little hotkey combo<br>
<br>
but a sarnak battleshield is 25 AC<br>
my BP is 25 AC...<br>
<br>
i always use my shield when i'm pulling and when i'm the main tank unless i really need to dual wield to taunt off someone with a really big agro like a necro or when i'm one of the main damage sources<br>
most of the time i can still taunt everything without dual wielding though so it's only a matter of damage<br>
<br>
trust me 25 AC + stuff = yum yum <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usindarrefrospaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sindarre Frospaw</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/9/00 10:13:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> Nah.. you are giving up way too much to use a shield.  16dmg 30dly is nice but not that great really.  30dly is slow for one..... in the main hand you will be losing a lot just from the damage bonus.  Remember reading that the offhand swings about 60% of the time with identicle delay weapons.  That is a lot of damage you are missing out on dealing.  Taunt factor goes south.. all that ac means nothing if the critter is shredding your ranger or worse.. cleric.<br>
<br>
It's a nice weapon.. slow for my tastes, but the ratio is better then anything warrior usable that is still around.  Dragon eye is better, my claw has the same ratio.  Claw is unique and the Dragon Eye has been moved to critter unknown.  <br>
<br>
It takes a lot to put me in a shield I guess.. in fact, I only know one place I do use a shield, and the only place I would.. sky.<br>
<br>
Sindarre Frostpaw<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/urykilth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykilth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/9/00 12:29:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cpl.net/~kurtds/pic/ryk.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> *Paladin nudges in* =)<br>
<br>
<br>
Heck, as far as shields go, I have a 18/25 weapon, (thanks again Silent Redemption) =)  and frankly, I still use my Fiery Avenger over it.  From some tests I've run, I think AC only factors in every 100points.  Seems I saw a reduction at 700, 800, 900, and 1000.   A shield will put me at the upper end of 900, but not close enough to 1000.  I do have a 1000AC gear set, but all my stats go south.  As a Hybrid, I'm stat reliant on Wisdom etc.  so I don't that gear unless it's Plane of Sky.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cents =) <p>--------------------------------<br>
Rykilth Spiritblade<BR>
Holy Knight of Mithaniel Marr<BR>
Brell Serilis Server<BR>
Officer of the Legion of Heroes
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=copeland>Copeland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/10/00 10:48:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> Actually, it's a nice weapon...but too slow.  In the hands of anyone 50+, there are a fair number of weapons that will do more damage simply due to the bonus.  By that point the ratio is not the most important component of the damage calculation...the bonus is.  In addition to those Sindarre mentions, Mosscovered Twig, Barbed Scale Whip, Jade Mace, Lamentation, Swordbreaker, Crystalline Short Sword, Jarsath Trident and several others are all better than the Jagged Long Sword.<br>
<br>
As for the shield, over a quarter of your damage comes from the off-hand.  If you don't need that, then the extra AC is nice.  If you're trying to keep the MOBs off the rangers, you might want to forgo the shield. <p><font color=8bb4d2 face="Garamond"><b>- Cope -</b></font></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=copeland>Copeland</A> at: 7/10/00 9:53:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dantes>Dantes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://forums.eqrealms.com/ubb/icons/icon10.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/11/00 1:32:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.valorblade.com/dantes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: sword+shield viable?</span><hr size=1> I would consider a shield useful at times, yet I'm only 46th level and sometimes in Karnor's I'm grouped with monks who are more than 5 levels higher than me.  I don't know if anyone has tried to taunt off of monk like Jagriel when he's using the Tranquil staff, but for me it's impossible.  With a Jarsath Trident and a Yak I can't even get them to turn even for a second.  I could just equip a shield with my trident and then be extra helpful during times when a 'Something of Sathir' tries to gate or a Curate tries to get a complete heal casted.  As a wood elf I don't have the slam option.<br>
<br>
But, then again the platinum doesn't exactly fall like rain for me and a nice shield hasn't fallen in my lap, so I'm not really going to make much effort to get one and definitely won't spend any money on it.  I guess either way if I deal more dmg the mob is going to fall faster so shield or not it probably doesn't make much difference.<br>
 <p><img src="http://www.valorblade.com/dantes2.jpg" width="305" height="138"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=28.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=24.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=22.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilisfrm64">Archived Threads<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: Races and Classes <option value="brellserilisroleplaying">Tome: History of Norrath<option value="brellserilisfrm49">T